@Andrzej it’s a pronunciation thing, particularly in American English: we often pronounce the D sound like a T and use schwas instead of stronger vowel sounds. So “Crossed a bear” sounds like “crost uh bare”, and “Cross to bear” sounds like “cross tuh bare”. 

BTW, I always love seeing your comments and am super impressed that you can do our very idiosyncratic American puzzles!

